			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=10450#M10450">76</a> of 95
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 97 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I think tradeskills are a really under developed feature in EQ. More attention to making the tradeskills a rewarding and enjoyable feature would add greatly to the games appeal. </P>
<P>One of the features I dislike that seems terribly unfair is making armor 'nodrop'. A lot of effort and expense goes into making armor or getting it as a drop from a mob or a quest... to make it then a nodrop item seems criminal. I cannot trade it to one of my other characters or friends or sell it to recoup the effort and labor I went to to acquire it...&nbsp; i think this should be changed in the game. </P>
<P>Also the value of tradeskill items and their stats should be superior to those of many of the drop items.... and quest armor should be very high in stats, and far superior to any other armor in the game. Adding augments should make specific desired changes to stats that are customized to the user... and this is a really neat idea. But we should not loose them unless they are easily acquired again for use on another weapon or piece of armor. </P>
<P>The Ultimate character enhancement should make one a god at their level... with the ability to perform all features of any character.. through ability or device or potion... or augment...&nbsp; and the only thing standing in the way of achieving that would be good player participation... </P>
<P>I think the tradeskills are one of the best things there are in the game... maybe being able to build cities on un developed land in the game would be the next logical step to improve the game.... </P>
<P>but I digress... </P>
<P><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Banks Lioneheart 
58th  Level Druid
Ayonae Ro Server
							</div>
								
