			>
			For me, I have a fairly high level toon in most standard tradeskills, and I find while there are many good things to make for people < 40 eg if you want to help up and comming toons, once a toon is in its 40s the majority of tradeskilled items which you desire to use are just almost non existant. Yet the mobs you need to make the stuff can be hard to find.<br><br>It would be nice if there were abilities change the colours of all items, like the tailored stuff, rather than just smithed stuff, and maybe imbue more things with some properties, with augments even if you like but ones you make and apply and it doesnt become nodrop.. so for example<br><br>I make a robe out of fine silk (obtained from say PoN spiders), it is say Ac 20<br>I make using pottery and say err alchemy an augment which adds +10 INT, +10 STA<br>I make using JC and say poison making an augment which adds Focus effect: summoning efficiency 3<br>I make using tailoring and poison making red and gold threads<br><br>(I point out here actually I dont have a rogue so I dont have poison making... but.. it could give them a better outlet in life)<br><br>I apply it all together in my sewing box and I come out with a Ac20, +10 int, +10 sta with summoning efficency 3 robe which when worn is by default red and gold.<br><br>Its such a shame that hand made stuff is often so dull to look at, after all, if I really were a 250 tailor, Id expect I could do some damn fine needlepoint on it!!!!<br><br>It would be so nice if we could make more useful things, even if many were self only..	
