			>
			<P>Again,</P>
<P>What about we agnostics?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Also,</P>
<P>Dwarves +10% AT?&nbsp; WTH?&nbsp; Why not to Direction sense?&nbsp; Oh wait, that too was nerfed when everyone got 200.&nbsp;&nbsp;You want to give something useful to almost every other race?&nbsp; What?&nbsp;&nbsp;Since when are barbarians more able to smith better than dwarves?&nbsp; And, at 10%?&nbsp; More than a GM tradeskill trophy?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I have no problem with your premise, but the execution needs a <STRONG>LOT </STRONG>more work.<BR></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Meryddian wrote:<BR>
<DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<DIV><STRONG>Another is racial tradeskills,</STRONG> these needs to be created for the new up and comming 65-70 game as well. <STRONG>Making racial smithing more on par with today's standards rather than the old world standard</STRONG>. Example is&nbsp;the discrepency between ogre to iksar. Ogre cultural is considered one of the most superior, yet iksar is considered one of the worst due to low ac. Pariety between each race/class is the way to balance things in trades. </DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>In general, I would love to see cultural armor be on par with EP-level tradeskilled/high end LDoN-purchaseable. This is a logical expectation, as high-end cultural armors are trivial at the same levels as EP armor (282+). Additionally,&nbsp;since it is player-made, and since diety-imbued armor was once the best you could get without accessing the likes of VT/Ssra etc,&nbsp;it would be nice&nbsp;if was like the GoD gear, where there is more augmentation choices (ie. type 2, 3 and 7 slots on armor; type 4, 5, 6 on weapons etc). Demand for cultural armor was greatly weakened with PoP, although there does remain a steady - if smaller - market these days.</P>
<P><STRONG>1 -- Would love to see, first and foremost, is to have existing racial recipes upgraded so that they can be imbued for <U>all dieties</U> that that specific race can make.</STRONG></P>
<P><EM>IE: Wood elves and High elves can only imbue their armor - whether it is silk, plate or chain - to Tunare. But there are tons of elves who worship the likes of Mithaniel Marr, Erollisi Marr, Bristlebane,&nbsp;etc. </EM></P>
<P>Currently the only race that can imbue their armor to more than one god is humans - are humans smarter than the rest of us? (well... we know what innate stats look like, we know that's not true. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> )&nbsp; And the poor Vah Shir and Frogloks do not have their own worthwhile cultural armor yet, either. What it does is gives humans a far more flexible niche in the trade market - after all, aren't humans the largest % among the population? </P>
<P>(Mmmm... and along those lines, will Barbarians on servers other than Sullon Zek ever be able to freely worship Mithaniel Marr? He is after all the god who created them!)</P>
<P><STRONG>2 -- Would love to see the diety-related jewelcraft receive some upgrades to make it worthwhile again to make&nbsp;</STRONG>- for example, there were never velium combines made, OR, with the discovery of new metals on the Taelosian continent, wouldn't it be possible to combine some of these new metals and gems with imbued gems to make more interesting jewelry? The new GoD jewelry fills some interesting niche slots, but currently the best crafted jewelry items are PoP items - which means the primary people making them are folks who're self-farming the materials out of the planes. (or folks who risk high pp loss by buying items in the&nbsp;Bazaar). Would be great to find that the old world gods can take these new metals and make them their own. Would be <EM>phenominal</EM> to see maybe some low end focii on diety- or cultural-based jewelry to give a kick back into the player-made JC market as well as giving alternative sources for focii than just dropped armor.<BR></P>
<DIV><STRONG>3 -- Would love to see the advent of cultural-based charms (/em wishlist augments too)</STRONG> - at one time, the diety-based pottery statuettes were not bad for the level; now they have far less use and the market for them has dropped considerably, especially for items trivial 200+. It would be awesome to see race-specific charms, or maybe ones that gained or lost power as you gained or lost favor/faction with that god/faction. They wouldn't have to be diety-based, but rather could be based on the race that makes them and give bonuses suitable to their race, it could be something "fun," doesn't necessarily have to be something like ATK or whatever:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Barbarian - 10% to smithing</DIV>
<DIV>Dark </DIV>
<DIV><FONT face=Helv size=2>
<P>Barbarian - 10% to smithing</P>
<P>Dark Elf - 10% to sneak</P>
<P>Dwarf - 10% to alcohol tolerance</P>
<P>Erudite - 10% to fishing </P>
<P>Froglok - Enduring breath</P>
<P>Gnome - 10% to tinkering </P>
<P>Half elf - clicky Alliance (faction mod)</P>
<P>Halfling - 10% to baking </P>
<P>High elf - 2% to evocation</P>
<P>Human - 2% to conjuration</P>
<P>Iksar - 10% to swimming </P>
<P>Ogre - 1% to stuns</P>
<P>Troll - +1 regen</P>
<P>Vah Shir - 10% to safe fall</P>
