<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=10466#M10466">94</a> of 95
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 97 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I do like the ideas of player-made augments and such.&nbsp; I just&nbsp;thought of a different method of using them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Augments would be made via tradeskills. Trivials would vary depending on what you are making.&nbsp; But the augments would not be used like LDoN augments are now.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Augments would be made and used by people making magic items of various types.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For example: A Wizard would locate the items needed to make an augment capable of casting a Bolt of Flame.&nbsp; It would have 1 charge.&nbsp; The wizard could then locate more components (or quest) to improve it to 2 (or more) charges.&nbsp; Once a certain number of charges is reached, allow the wizard to do something different to allow said augment to have a "Proc" effect.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In combination with the augments, items could be crafted and fitted wth augments.&nbsp; Here is an example:&nbsp; A&nbsp;Fine Steel Two-Handed Sword could have a total of 6 slots (3 Stat, 2 Resist, and 1 Special).&nbsp; The person crafting the item would either make or purchase the augments from other players and combine them with the sword.&nbsp; An additional limitation on this could be the type of metal used to make the weapon.&nbsp; A Fine Steel 2 Handed Sord would be limited to +5 Stats, +10 Resists, and One special ability.&nbsp; A Velium Two Handed Sword could be given extra slots (4 Stats, 3 Resist, and 2 Special) with limits at +10 Stats, +15 or +20 resists, and 2 special abilities.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Then the Wizard can work with someone else to add the augment to a magic item and allow the item to have a Bolt of Flame proc. Enchanters would probably be the only ones that would be able to make the maga regen augments.&nbsp; And the major healers would be good candidates for the hp regen augments.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This would allow players to craft custom items and configure them as they want.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What does everyone think?</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
